comments: Towns (MIN) makes contact to Aldridge's (SAS) arm during his shooting motion and contact affects his shot attempt.
Edwards (MIN) and Murray (SAS) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Towns (MIN) firms up in a legal screening position in DeRozan's (SAS) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
DeRozan (SAS) gathers the ball on his left foot and then takes three steps.
Edwards (MIN) makes marginal contact to DeRozan (SAS) defending his driving shot attempt.
Mills (SAS) and Russell (MIN) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Murray (SAS) makes marginal contact with Towns' (MIN) arm as he goes to tip in the rebound.
Murray (SAS) maintains a legal pivot foot.
Edwards (MIN) delivers contact to DeRozan's (SAS) body during his shooting motion that affects his driving shot attempt.
Russell (MIN) straddles the lane line and is in the lane for longer than three seconds without actively guarding an opponent.
Towns (MIN) establishes himself in a screening position in Murray's (SAS) path firming up and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Towns (MIN) makes incidental "high-five" contact with DeRozan (SAS) after the release that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Towns (MIN) establishes legal position in Murray's (SAS) path during the pick and makes some contact as they disengage.
Aldridge (SAS) makes incidental contact to Russell's (MIN) body after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Aldridge (SAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Culver's (MIN) path and makes some contact as they disengage.
Culver (MIN) makes contact with the ball during DeRozan's (SAS) shooting motion and dislodges the ball defending his driving shot attempt. Any ensuing contact is deemed incidental.
Murray (SAS) and Russell (MIN) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Russell (MIN) releases from contact with Mills (SAS) prior to his jump shot attempt.
Vanderbilt (MIN) makes incidental contact to Johnson (SAS) after the release of his shot attempt at the basket.
Russell (MIN) makes marginal contact to Murray (SAS) during his drive to the basket and he is able to move through contact.
Russell (MIN) makes contact with the ball during Murray's (SAS) shooting motion and dislodges the ball defending his driving shot attempt. Any ensuing contact is deemed incidental.
Towns (MIN) makes contact with Johnson's (SAS) arm during his shooting motion that affects the play at the basket.
Towns (MIN) brushes Johnson's (SAS) arm as they engage and the contact does not affect his ability to retrieve the loose ball.
Mills (SAS) moves laterally in Russell's (SAS) path during at the start of his drive and contact affects his SQBR.
Murray (SAS) makes marginal contact to Towns' (MIN) front contesting his shot attempt at the basket.
Towns (MIN) establishes himself in a screening position in Murray's (SAS) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Johnson (SAS) makes incidental contact to Beasley's (SAS) body after the release of his jump shot.
Edwards (MIN) makes incidental "high-five" contact with DeRozan (SAS) after the release of his jump shot attempt.
